git commands
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
  1) git config --global user.name "enter user name"
  2) git config --global user.email "enter email"--->here double quote not required
       -->if you strat fresh project take url and clone to folder
  3) git clone repository url
       -->after that inside your given path one folder will be created so that using cmd cd set path again then do 
  4) git init
       -->to add all files
  5) git add .
  6) git add <filename>
       -->to commit file
  7) git commit -m "message"
      -->to push to repository
  8) git push or git push origin master  git push -u origin master
      -->you want copy file from repository to local repository/project
  9) git pull
      -->to crate new branch
  10) git checkout -b <give name for branch" to create> ex:abc
      -->switch to master branch
  11) git checkout master
      -->switch to local branch
  12) git checkout abc
      -->to check whether your in master branch/remote
  13) git remote
  14) git remote -v
       -->to add branch
  15) git remote add origin <give url here>
      -->to copy file from master branch to local first we need to switch to the master branch  and pull it
  16) git pull origin master
      -->checkout to local branch 
  17) git checkout abc
      -->my local branch is now abc---> and i am here do 
  18) git pull origin master
      -->to check which branch your are in do
  19) git branch
      -->to check modified file do it will show all untracked files(ex : two files i have )
  20) git status
      -->to add to branch do  
  21) git add file1
      --> check again
  22) git status 
      -->when i did git status i will display  1 untracked file so i don't want ton see it then do
  23) git stash
      -->to check this do
  24) git status 
      -->here 1 untraked file will not display
      --> again i want to see it again means just do
  25) git stash pop
        or 
  26) git stash apply


